# USDrop V3 Development Guidelines

## Component Development Standards

### Brand Tokens & Theming
- **Always use brand tokens** from `globals.css` CSS variables instead of hardcoded colors
- Use semantic color tokens: `primary`, `secondary`, `accent`, `muted`, `foreground`, `background`, etc.
- For purple/orange brand colors, use `primary` and `accent` tokens which are already configured
- Use `text-foreground`, `bg-background`, `border-border`, etc. for consistent theming
- Support dark mode by using theme-aware classes (dark mode is handled automatically via CSS variables)

### Shadcn UI Components
- **Always use shadcn components** from `@/components/ui` when available
- When creating new components, check if a shadcn equivalent exists first
- Install new shadcn components using: `npx shadcn@latest add [component-name] --yes`
- Follow shadcn patterns and composition for consistency
- Use shadcn variants and props instead of custom styling when possible

### Component Structure
- Place all components in `src/components/` directory
- UI primitives go in `src/components/ui/` (shadcn components)
- Feature-specific components go in `src/components/` root
- Use TypeScript for all components
- Use "use client" directive for client-side interactivity

### Styling Guidelines
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Prefer composition over customization
- Use `cn()` utility from `@/lib/utils` for conditional classes
- Follow the existing design system patterns
- Maintain consistent spacing using Tailwind's spacing scale
- Use semantic HTML elements with appropriate ARIA attributes

### File Organization
- Keep components focused and single-purpose
- Export components from index files when appropriate
- Use descriptive, PascalCase names for components
- Match file names to component names

### Best Practices
- Always adapt new components to use brand tokens automatically
- Ensure components work in both light and dark modes
- Test responsive behavior (mobile-first approach)
- Use shadcn's built-in accessibility features
- Follow Next.js 16+ patterns (App Router, Server/Client Components)

### Example Component Pattern
```tsx
"use client" // if needed

import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
import { Card } from "@/components/ui/card"

export function MyComponent({ className, ...props }: React.ComponentProps<"div">) {
  return (
    <Card className={cn("p-6", className)} {...props}>
      <Button variant="default">Action</Button>
    </Card>
  )
}
```

## Project-Specific Notes
- Project location: `usdrop-v3/`
- Theme: Purple/Orange gradient brand colors
- Framework: Next.js 16+ with App Router
- UI Library: Shadcn UI (New York style)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS v4 with CSS variables

